The sport most often referred to as the "sport of kings" is:

Polo:
Here's why:

Polo has a long history of association with royalty, nobility, and the elite.
Historically, it was a sport favored by kings and members of royal courts.
Its origins trace back to ancient Persia, where it was played by noble warriors.
Even in modern times, polo retains an image of exclusivity and high society.
